            . I lodge at the <placeName id="t18091101-77-crimeloc471">Elephant and Castle, Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18091101-77-crimeloc471" type="placeName" value="Elephant and Castle, Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18091101-77-crimeloc471" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18091101-77-off469 t18091101-77-crimeloc471"></join>. On the 12th of October I was sitting in the tap room, breakfasting; I placed two five shilling papers of halfpence on the seat, and covered them over. The prisoner came in and set by my side.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you miss any part of your halfpence - A.One of the papers were broke into, and three shillings and sixpence were taken out, after I had finished my breakfast I removed two or three yards to look at a newspaper. A constable was sent for, and eighty four halfpence were taken out of the prisoner's pocket.</p>
               <p>- HUTCHINS. I am a constable. I searched the prisoner and took eighty-four halfpence from him. He denied having them.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was a little in liquor; I do not remember the circumstance.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18091101-77-verdict472" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18091101-77-verdict472" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
